Turkey will fight terrorism &#8220;right to the end,&#8221; President Recep Tayyip Erdogan said on Sunday following twin blasts in Istanbul that killed 38 people.&#8220;My country and my people can rest assured: that we will fight the scourge of terrorism right to the end. We will not leave (the attacks) go unpunished. They (the attackers) will pay a heavy price,&#8221; he told a news conference in Istanbul.-AFP